                <head>77. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_REO1">Reischauer</persName> submitted his
                    resignation in April and left Japan on August 19, 1966, to resume his academic
                    career at Harvard University. He explains his reasons for leaving in <hi
                        rend="italic">My Life Between Japan and America</hi>, pages 295–297 and
                    301.</p>
                <p>Shortly before his departure from Tokyo, Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_REO1"
                        >Reischauer</persName> wrote a lengthy critique of U.S. policy toward the
                    People’s Republic of China and its effects on United States-Japan relations.
                    That document, telegram 1126 from Tokyo, August 11, is printed in <ref
                        target="frus1964-68v30#d174">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1964–1968, volume XXX, Document
                        174</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
